tables.name: SalesLT.Customer
tables.description: The SalesLT.Customer table stores information about customers, including their personal details and contact information. Each customer is uniquely identified by a CustomerID, which serves as the primary key. The table includes attributes such as names, related company details, contact details like email and phone, and information about associated sales personnel. It also contains security-related information for customer authentication, such as hashed passwords and cryptographic salts. Data modification tracking is facilitated through the ModifiedDate column.

columns.name: CustomerID
columns.definition: The CustomerID column is an integer that serves as the primary key in the SalesLT.Customer table. It uniquely identifies each customer in the database. This column contains numeric values that are assigned sequentially to each new customer record. As a primary key, it ensures that each customer can be uniquely referenced and related to other data within the database system.

columns.name: NameStyle
columns.definition: The NameStyle column in the SalesLT.Customer table is a bit value that indicates whether the customer's name is in a predefined format. A value of 0 (or false) means the name follows a non-predefined format, while a value of 1 (or true) indicates that a predefined format is used. This column helps in determining how to process and display customer names accordingly.

columns.name: Title
columns.definition: The Title column in the SalesLT.Customer table contains the honorifics or titles associated with customers. These titles may include common prefixes such as Mr., Ms., Sr., and Sra., which are used to address or refer to individuals formally. The data type for this column is nvarchar, indicating that it can hold variable-length Unicode characters. The Title column is not a primary key and typically contains short, standardized text strings. This column may be useful for sorting, filtering, or categorizing customer records in queries.

columns.name: FirstName
columns.definition: The FirstName column in the SalesLT.Customer table contains the first names of customers. This column stores the first part of the customer's full name, which can include initials or full names. It is an nvarchar type, allowing for a variety of characters to accommodate different name formats. This column is not a primary key but is essential for customer identification and record-keeping.

columns.name: MiddleName
columns.definition: The "MiddleName" column in the "SalesLT.Customer" table contains the middle names of customers. This column stores values as strings in the nvarchar format, which means it can include characters and numbers. The middle name may be a single letter or a full name. This column may contain NULL values if the middle name is not provided.

columns.name: LastName
columns.definition: The LastName column in the SalesLT.Customer table contains the last names of customers. This column is of type nvarchar, indicating it can store variable-length Unicode strings. It includes common family names which are used to identify and differentiate individuals within the customer dataset. This information is often utilized for customer identification, sorting, and searching purposes in queries.

columns.name: Suffix
columns.definition: The "Suffix" column in the SalesLT.Customer table contains suffixes that may be appended to a customer's name, such as "Jr.", "Sr.", "II", "IV", and "PhD". This column is of type nvarchar and is used to store string values representing various suffixes that denote generational or professional titles. The information in this column helps to provide more specific identification and personalization of individuals within the customer database.

columns.name: CompanyName
columns.definition: The CompanyName column in the SalesLT.Customer table contains the names of various companies associated with the customers. This column stores textual data representing the full names of these companies. It helps identify which company a particular customer is affiliated with. The data type is nvarchar, indicating that it can store variable-length Unicode strings. This column is not used as a primary key.

columns.name: SalesPerson
columns.definition: The SalesPerson column in the SalesLT.Customer table contains the usernames of the sales representatives associated with each customer. The data comprises unique usernames in the format "adventure-works\\username" which represents the salespeople who manage or are assigned to these customers. This column is of type nvarchar and helps to identify the responsible salesperson for interactions and transactions with the customer. This column can be used to filter customer data based on the assigned salesperson.

columns.name: EmailAddress
columns.definition: The EmailAddress column in the SalesLT.Customer table contains the email addresses of customers. This column stores the email addresses as strings (nvarchar) and each entry is unique to a customer. It is used to facilitate communication with customers and may be utilized for services such as notifications, newsletters, order confirmations, and other customer interactions. This column does not allow null values to ensure every customer record has a valid email address associated with it.

columns.name: Phone
columns.definition: The "Phone" column in the SalesLT.Customer table contains phone numbers associated with each customer. The data type for this column is nvarchar, indicating that the phone numbers are stored as variable-length Unicode character strings. The phone numbers follow a specific format that includes country code, area code, and the main number. This column is crucial for customer contact and communication purposes.

columns.name: PasswordHash
columns.definition: The PasswordHash column in the SalesLT.Customer table contains hashed representations of the customers' passwords. These hashed values are generated using a cryptographic hashing function to ensure password security and are stored as varchar data types. Each entry in this column represents a unique, encrypted format of the customer's original password, making it challenging to retrieve the plain text version without the appropriate hashing key and salt. This column is crucial for authentication and verification processes during customer login.

columns.name: PasswordSalt
columns.definition: The PasswordSalt column in the SalesLT.Customer table contains a string value used as a cryptographic salt in hashing customer passwords. The salt is appended or prepended to the password before applying the hashing algorithm to ensure uniqueness and enhance security. This process helps to protect the passwords against common attack vectors such as rainbow table attacks. The data in this column is essential for the authentication process to verify the password entered by a user.

columns.name: rowguid
columns.definition: The rowguid column in the SalesLT.Customer table is a uniqueidentifier field that stores globally unique identifier (GUID) values. This column is typically used to ensure the uniqueness of records, especially when merging or synchronizing datasets across different databases or systems. The GUID values in this column are automatically generated and do not follow a sequential order. The rowguid column helps in avoiding record duplication and maintaining the integrity of the data.

columns.name: ModifiedDate
columns.definition: The ModifiedDate column in the SalesLT.Customer table represents the date and time when the customer record was last modified. The data type for this column is datetime, which typically includes both the date and the time of modification. This information is crucial for tracking changes to customer records, enabling data consistency and audit trails. Queries involving this column may often filter or sort records based on the most recent modifications.

tables.name: SalesLT.Product
tables.description: The SalesLT.Product table is a comprehensive inventory of products held by a business. It contains detailed information about each product, including unique identifiers, names, product numbers, cost and price details, and attributes such as color, size, and weight. The table also includes categorical data linking products to specific categories and models, along with various dates indicating the product's availability and status. Additional columns store metadata such as images and GUIDs, which help in managing and querying the product records effectively.

columns.name: ProductID
columns.definition: The ProductID column in the SalesLT.Product table is an integer that serves as the primary key for identifying products. Each ProductID is unique to each product, ensuring that no two products share the same identifier. This column is used to reference specific products in the database and is essential for product identification and relationship establishment with other tables.

columns.name: Name
columns.definition: The "Name" column in the SalesLT.Product table stores the names of the products. It is an nvarchar data type, indicating that it holds Unicode variable-length character strings, which can include letters, numbers, and special characters. This column is not the primary key, meaning it is not required to have unique values for every product. The values in this column represent descriptive names that can include product types, attributes, and features.

columns.name: ProductNumber
columns.definition: The column ProductNumber in the SalesLT.Product table contains the unique identifier for each product in the form of a string. These values typically represent product codes or SKUs that are distinct for each item. This column is essential for distinguishing between different products and may be used in operations like joining tables, filtering, and referencing specific products in queries.

columns.name: Color
columns.definition: The "Color" column in the SalesLT.Product table is an nvarchar type that stores the color of each product. This column contains descriptive text values indicating the color or color combinations, such as "Black," "Blue," "Silver/Black," etc. It is not a mandatory field and may have multiple distinct values representing different products in various colors. This column can be used to filter products based on their color attributes in SQL queries.

columns.name: StandardCost
columns.definition: The StandardCost column in the SalesLT.Product table represents the cost of manufacturing or purchasing a product. It is a monetary value stored in the 'money' data type, indicating the base cost associated with each product listed. This cost information is crucial for financial analysis, pricing strategies, and profitability assessments. The data in this column does not include any taxes, shipping costs, or other additional expenses.

columns.name: ListPrice
columns.definition: The ListPrice column in the SalesLT.Product table contains monetary values that represent the retail price at which each product is listed for sale. This column is of the 'money' data type and records the price set for each product before any discounts or promotions are applied. The ListPrice is crucial for evaluating the sale price of products and can be used to calculate revenue or apply pricing policies. This column can be used in SQL queries to filter products based on their retail price or to perform aggregate calculations like finding the average list price of products.

columns.name: Size
columns.definition: The "Size" column in the "SalesLT.Product" table contains values representing the size specifications of various products. The data type is "nvarchar", indicating that the size could be numerical or alphanumerical characters. These sizes are typically used to denote the physical dimensions or fitting categories of products. This column helps in classifying the products based on their size for inventory, sales, and marketing purposes.

columns.name: Weight
columns.definition: The "Weight" column in the SalesLT.Product table represents the weight of each product. The data type is decimal and can accommodate floating point values, allowing for precise measurements. This column may contain missing values, represented as NaN, indicating that the weight for some products is not specified. It is useful for filtering and analyzing products based on their weight.

columns.name: ProductCategoryID
columns.definition: ProductCategoryID is an integer column in the SalesLT.Product table that represents the category to which a product belongs. Each unique integer value corresponds to a different product category, linking products to their respective categories. This column is used to categorize and organize products, facilitating easier search, filtering, and analysis based on product categories. It is not a primary key but is essential for understanding the grouping of different products within the database.

columns.name: ProductModelID
columns.definition: ProductModelID is an integer column in the SalesLT.Product table that represents the ID of the model to which a product belongs. This column is used to categorize products based on their model type. Each ProductModelID corresponds to a specific product model within the database, facilitating the organization and retrieval of product information by model.

columns.name: SellStartDate
columns.definition: SellStartDate is a datetime column in the SalesLT.Product table that records the date when a specific product became available for sale. This column is essential for tracking the sale history and availability of a product. It helps in determining the product's lifecycle and can be used to filter products available for sale within a specific date range. This information is crucial for sales analysis and inventory management.

columns.name: SellEndDate
columns.definition: SellEndDate in the SalesLT.Product table indicates the date when a product stops being available for sale. This is a datetime column that can contain null values for products still available for sale. SellEndDate helps in determining the duration for which a product was or will be on the market and is useful for filtering products based on their availability period.

columns.name: DiscontinuedDate
columns.definition: The DiscontinuedDate column in the SalesLT.Product table records the date when a product was discontinued and is no longer available for sale. This column contains datetime values to specify the exact date a discontinuation took place. If the product is still active and available for sale, this column may be null. The data contained in this column is useful for queries that need to filter out discontinued products or determine the timeline of product availability.

columns.name: ThumbNailPhoto
columns.definition: The ThumbNailPhoto column in the SalesLT.Product table stores the binary data for the thumbnail images that represent the products. This column contains small-sized image files in a binary format (varbinary), which are often used for displaying a quick preview of the product. Each entry in this column corresponds to a product identified by the ProductID primary key. The binary data in this column can be used to render thumbnail photos in applications or reports.

columns.name: ThumbnailPhotoFileName
columns.definition: The column ThumbnailPhotoFileName in the SalesLT.Product table stores the file names of thumbnail images associated with each product. These file names are of type nvarchar and typically include the product name or description along with an indicator of the image size (e.g., small). This column does not contain actual photo data but rather the identifier for the photo, which can be used to retrieve or display the thumbnail image related to the respective product.

columns.name: rowguid
columns.definition: The column "rowguid" in the "SalesLT.Product" table is a unique identifier for each product using the GUID (Globally Unique Identifier) format. This column ensures that each product has a distinct and non-duplicable identifier, which is crucial for differentiating records even if other column values are the same. The values in this column are automatically generated and follow the standard GUID format, making it ideal for scenarios where a unique key is needed across tables and databases.

columns.name: ModifiedDate
columns.definition: The ModifiedDate column in the SalesLT.Product table contains datetime values that indicate the most recent date and time when the product record was updated. These datetime values reflect the precise moment a change was made to any details related to the product, such as pricing, descriptions, or specifications. This column is crucial for tracking the history of product data alterations and ensuring that the information is up to date.

tables.name: SalesLT.ProductCategory
tables.description: The SalesLT.ProductCategory table is used to store information about different product categories within the database. Each category is uniquely identified by a primary key and can have a hierarchical relationship with other categories via parent-child associations. The table stores descriptive names for the categories and uses unique identifiers for data integrity. Additionally, it tracks the modification date and time for each record to maintain update history. This organization helps in efficient categorization and retrieval of product information.

columns.name: ProductCategoryID
columns.definition: The ProductCategoryID column is an integer primary key that uniquely identifies each product category in the SalesLT.ProductCategory table. This column contains distinct numerical identifiers for each category, ensuring that each category can be individually referenced. It is essential for linking product categories to other tables and for querying specific categories within the product catalog.

columns.name: ParentProductCategoryID
columns.definition: The ParentProductCategoryID column in the SalesLT.ProductCategory table is an integer that indicates the parent category for a given product category. This column helps establish hierarchical relationships between product categories, where each category can have a parent category, creating a tree structure. If the value is NULL or NaN, it indicates that the category is a top-level category without a parent. This column is used to organize and categorize products in a structured manner, facilitating search and navigation.

columns.name: Name
columns.definition: The Name column in the SalesLT.ProductCategory table contains the names of product categories. It is of type nvarchar and stores descriptive names such as "Accessories" or "Bikes." This column is not a primary key but is crucial for identifying and categorizing different types of products in the database. The values in this column are used to label product categories and may be employed for filtering and sorting operations in queries.

columns.name: rowguid
columns.definition: The column rowguid in the SalesLT.ProductCategory table contains a uniqueidentifier for each record in the table. This is used to ensure the uniqueness of each product category entry and can be utilized for tracking or referencing specific rows across various operations. The values in this column are globally unique, represented in the format of a UUID, ensuring no two entries will have the same identifier. Such a column is crucial for maintaining data integrity, especially in distributed systems or replication scenarios.

columns.name: ModifiedDate
columns.definition: The ModifiedDate column in the SalesLT.ProductCategory table captures the date and time when a record was last updated. It stores this information in the datetime format, which includes both the date and the time of modification. This column is important for tracking changes and maintaining the history of updates to product category records. Queries utilizing this column often filter data based on specific time frames or retrieve records that have been modified since a certain date.

tables.name: SalesLT.SalesOrderDetail
tables.description: The SalesLT.SalesOrderDetail table stores detailed information related to individual sales orders. Each row in the table represents a specific line item within a sales order, including details such as the product ordered, quantity, unit price, and any applicable discounts. The table facilitates the tracking, management, and analysis of sales transactions by linking order details to their respective sales orders. This table is essential for generating accurate sales reports and analyzing revenue.

columns.name: SalesOrderID
columns.definition: SalesOrderID is an integer column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderDetail table that serves as a unique identifier for each sales order. It is a primary key in this table and ensures that each sales order can be uniquely identified and referenced. The column is used to link sales order details with their respective sales orders, facilitating accurate data retrieval and management for sales transactions. Each SalesOrderID corresponds to a specific sales order, allowing for effective organization and tracking of order records within the database.

columns.name: SalesOrderID
columns.definition: The SalesOrderID column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderDetail table is an integer that uniquely identifies each sales order. It serves as a primary key and is used to connect sales order details to specific sales orders. This column is essential for tracking individual sales transactions and ensuring accurate record-keeping within the sales database.

columns.name: SalesOrderDetailID
columns.definition: SalesOrderDetailID is an integer column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderDetail table, serving as one of the primary keys. It uniquely identifies each detail line associated with a sales order. This column ensures that every order detail record can be distinctly recognized and referenced individually within the table.

columns.name: OrderQty
columns.definition: The OrderQty column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderDetail table represents the quantity of the product ordered in a particular sales order. This column contains small integer values indicating the number of units of the product included in each order line. The OrderQty column is crucial for calculating the total quantity of products sold in sales reports and inventory management.

columns.name: ProductID
columns.definition: The ProductID column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderDetail table represents the unique identifier for each product included in the sales order details. It is an integer value that links to products in the inventory and is used to specify which product is associated with each sales order detail entry. This column is not a primary key but is essential in identifying the product being ordered.

columns.name: UnitPrice
columns.definition: The UnitPrice column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderDetail table represents the price of each product unit at the time of the sale. The data type is money, indicating that it stores monetary values with a fixed precision. This column is critical for calculations related to total sales and revenue analysis. It can be used to determine the cost per unit of various products included in sales orders. This column does not include any discounts or taxes.

columns.name: UnitPriceDiscount
columns.definition: The UnitPriceDiscount column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderDetail table represents the discount applied to the unit price of a product in a sales order. It is measured in monetary terms and reflects the reduction from the original unit price. This column helps in calculating the final price payable by factoring in the discount. The data in this column can vary, with possible values ranging from 0.0 to positive monetary amounts.

columns.name: LineTotal
columns.definition: The LineTotal column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderDetail table represents the total cost for each line item in a sales order. It is calculated as the product of OrderQty and UnitPrice, taking into account any UnitPriceDiscount that might be applied. The data type is numeric, indicating that this column contains monetary values. This column is crucial for identifying the total revenue generated from each line item in a sales order.

columns.name: rowguid
columns.definition: The rowguid column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderDetail table is used to store a unique identifier for each row, ensuring each entry can be distinctly identified. This column contains data of the uniqueidentifier type, which typically consists of GUIDs (Globally Unique Identifiers). These GUIDs are unique across space and time, providing a robust means of row identification. The rowguid column is not a primary key but acts as a unique reference to support data integrity and uniqueness within the table.

columns.name: ModifiedDate
columns.definition: The ModifiedDate column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderDetail table stores the date and time when the record was last modified. This column is of the datetime data type, indicating the specific point in time when changes were made to each sales order detail. It is essential for tracking the most recent updates to the records and can be used for filtering data based on modification times.

tables.name: SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader
tables.description: The SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table stores information related to sales orders in the database. Each sales order is uniquely identified by the SalesOrderID, and the table contains details such as order dates, shipping and billing information, customer and account identifiers, order status, and financial details like subtotal, tax amount, freight, and total due. This table is integral for tracking, managing, and analyzing sales order data, helping businesses maintain order records, oversee logistics, control financial transactions, and ensure customer satisfaction.

columns.name: SalesOrderID
columns.definition: SalesOrderID is an integer column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table that uniquely identifies each sales order. As the primary key, it ensures that each sales order record in the table is distinct. This ID is used to track and reference specific sales orders within the database, facilitating various operations such as querying, updating, and managing sales order information.

columns.name: RevisionNumber
columns.definition: The RevisionNumber column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table is used to track changes made to a sales order. This column holds an integer value that is incremented each time a modification is made to ensure the correct version of the order is being referenced. It is a tinyint type, indicating it can store values from 0 to 255. This column is essential for maintaining the integrity and version control of sales order records.

columns.name: OrderDate
columns.definition: The OrderDate column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table represents the date on which the sales order was placed. The data type of this column is datetime, indicating that it stores both the date and time information. This column is crucial for understanding the timeline of sales orders and tracking when specific orders were made. The values in this column are used to filter and sort sales orders based on their creation date.

columns.name: DueDate
columns.definition: The DueDate column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table contains datetime values representing the scheduled date by which a sales order is due to be completed or delivered. This column is crucial for tracking order deadlines and ensuring that products are delivered to customers on time. The values in this column help in managing logistics and customer satisfaction by providing a clear timeline for order fulfillment.

columns.name: ShipDate
columns.definition: The ShipDate column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table represents the date when the sales order was shipped to the customer. This column contains datetime values, indicating the specific date and time the shipment occurred. It is used to track when the order left the warehouse or shipping facility, which is essential for delivery tracking and inventory management purposes.

columns.name: Status
columns.definition: The "Status" column in the "SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader" table is a tinyint data type that indicates the current status of a sales order. This column typically holds numerical values that correspond to different predefined statuses, such as pending, completed, or cancelled. Each status value helps in tracking and managing the progress or state of a sales order through its lifecycle in the sales process.

columns.name: OnlineOrderFlag
columns.definition: The OnlineOrderFlag column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table is a bit type that indicates whether the sales order was placed online. If the value is 1 (true), it means the order was submitted through an online platform, otherwise, if the value is 0 (false), it was submitted through other channels such as phone or in-store. This column helps in distinguishing online orders from offline orders within the sales order data.

columns.name: SalesOrderNumber
columns.definition: The SalesOrderNumber column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table contains unique identifiers for sales orders in the form of NVARCHAR strings. These identifiers are typically prefixed with "SO" followed by a sequence of digits that differentiate each sales order. It is used to track and reference individual sales orders within the system, ensuring that each order can be uniquely identified and managed. This column is particularly important for joining order-related data across different tables and for retrieving specific sales order details.

columns.name: PurchaseOrderNumber
columns.definition: The PurchaseOrderNumber column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table contains alphanumeric strings uniquely identifying purchase orders associated with sales orders. This column is used to track and distinguish different purchase orders within the system. The values typically follow a specific format and are essential for mapping sales orders to their corresponding purchase documentation. This column helps in organizing and retrieving purchase order information efficiently for reporting and analysis purposes.

columns.name: AccountNumber
columns.definition: AccountNumber is a column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table that contains the unique alphanumeric identifier assigned to a customer's account. This column helps in identifying and managing individual customer accounts associated with the sales order. AccountNumber is typically formatted with a series of numbers and hyphens, for example, "10-4020-000006". It is used to link sales orders back to the specific accounts of the customers.

columns.name: CustomerID
columns.definition: The CustomerID column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table contains integer values representing unique identifiers for customers who have placed sales orders. This column is used to link the sales order to the specific customer, typically by referencing the CustomerID in another table where customer details are stored. Filtering queries based on this column would allow for retrieving orders corresponding to particular customers.

columns.name: ShipToAddressID
columns.definition: The ShipToAddressID column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table contains integer values that represent the unique identifier for the address where the order should be shipped. This column is used to link sales orders to specific shipping addresses, ensuring that each order is delivered to the correct location. The ShipToAddressID helps in managing the logistics and tracking of shipments for each sales order.

columns.name: BillToAddressID
columns.definition: BillToAddressID is an integer column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table that represents the unique identifier for the billing address associated with a sales order. This column is used to reference the address to which the invoice for the sales order will be sent. It ensures that each sales order has a corresponding billing address for accurate invoicing and record-keeping. This column is essential for differentiating between various billing addresses when processing sales orders.

columns.name: ShipMethod
columns.definition: The ShipMethod column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table indicates the method of shipping used for the sales order. This column typically contains descriptive text representing different shipping methods. The information in this column helps in identifying the logistics provider or the type of shipping service utilized. Analyzing this column can provide insights into the distribution and delivery patterns for sales orders.

columns.name: CreditCardApprovalCode
columns.definition: The CreditCardApprovalCode column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table contains alphanumeric codes that signify the authorization of credit card transactions for sales orders. These codes are provided by the credit card issuer once the transaction has been successfully approved. They are used to verify and record that the payment for an order has been authorized. This column is crucial for financial transactions and is typically unique for each approved credit card transaction within the sales order records.

columns.name: SubTotal
columns.definition: The SubTotal column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table represents the sum of all item amounts before taxes and shipping charges are applied. This value is calculated in monetary terms and provides a reference for the total cost of items in an order prior to additional costs like taxes (TaxAmt) and freight (Freight). The SubTotal column is essential for calculating the final total due for a sales order.

columns.name: TaxAmt
columns.definition: TaxAmt in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table represents the amount of tax applied to a sales order. This column stores monetary values reflecting the tax calculated based on the order's subtotal. The TaxAmt is essential for financial and sales reporting, allowing the determination of the total tax revenue. It is important to ensure the accuracy of this value for correct invoice generation and accounting records.

columns.name: Freight
columns.definition: The Freight column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table stores monetary values representing the shipping cost associated with each sales order. These costs are additional charges applied to the orders based on factors such as weight, shipping method, and distance. The data type for this column is money, indicating it handles currency values. Filtering this column can help in analyzing the shipping expenses and overall cost incurred on sales orders.

columns.name: TotalDue
columns.definition: The "TotalDue" column in the "SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader" table represents the total monetary amount due for each sales order. This value includes the subtotal, tax, and freight amounts combined to give the final amount that needs to be paid for the order. It is stored as a money data type and is crucial for financial calculations and order processing within the sales order header. This column is used to determine the complete financial obligation for the customer per sales order.

columns.name: Comment
columns.definition: The Comment column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table is of type nvarchar and holds textual data related to specific sales orders. This column is used to store any additional remarks or information provided by the customer or sales representative pertaining to the order. The content of this column might include special handling instructions, customer feedback, or other relevant notes. This column can help provide context or additional details that are not captured by other structured data columns.

columns.name: rowguid
columns.definition: The rowguid column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table is a unique identifier of type uniqueidentifier. It is used to ensure each row in the table has a globally unique identifier, which can be useful for synchronizing data across databases or systems. The values in this column are automatically generated and appear as a combination of numbers and letters, structured to avoid duplication. While it is not a primary key, it provides an additional layer of uniqueness for each sales order record.

columns.name: ModifiedDate
columns.definition: The ModifiedDate column in the SalesLT.SalesOrderHeader table represents the date and time when the sales order record was last updated or modified. This column contains datetime values, which include both the date and time components. It is used to track changes to the record and ensure that the data reflects the most recent modifications. This column is important for auditing and version control purposes.
